msgid "You can configure both Ollama and Claude at the same time and assign a different provider to each agent (hybrid setup)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:39
msgid "Step 1 — Install the Modules"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:41
msgid "Go to the **Apps** menu."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:42
msgid "Search for **\"Linkup AI\"**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:43
msgid "Install **Linkup AI Side Panel** (`lu_ai_sidepanel`). The required base modules (`ai_app`, `web_enterprise`) are installed automatically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:45
msgid "Install at least one **provider connector**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:46
msgid "**Linkup AI Ollama** (`lu_ai_ollama`) — local LLM via Ollama"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:47
msgid "**Linkup AI Claude** (`lu_ai_claude`) — cloud LLM via Anthropic Claude"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:48
msgid "Both can be installed simultaneously for a hybrid setup."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:51
msgid "`lu_ai_sidepanel` auto-installs `ai_app` and `web_enterprise`. The provider connectors (`lu_ai_ollama`, `lu_ai_claude`) must be installed separately — install one or both."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:55
msgid "Linkup AI Side Panel and Linkup AI Claude in the Apps list"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:55
msgid ".. image:: /_static/img/ai-agent/qs-install-modules.png"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:60
msgid "Step 2 — Configure Your LLM Provider"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:63
msgid "Ollama and Claude are configured on **separate Settings pages**. Setting up both providers lets you choose a provider per agent in Step 3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:67
msgid "Option A: Ollama (Local LLM)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:69
msgid "Go to **Settings → Integrations**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:70
msgid "Enable the **\"Use local Ollama models\"** toggle."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:71
msgid "Enter your Ollama server address in the URL field (placeholder: `http://localhost:11434`). If Ollama is running locally, leave the default value as-is."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:73
msgid "*(Optional)* API key field (placeholder: `API Key (optional for local setup)`) — only required for remote or authenticated endpoints. Leave blank for local installs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:75
#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:95
#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:121
msgid "Click **Save**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:78
msgid "The fields have no visible labels — only placeholder text. Refer to the screenshot below to locate them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:82
msgid "Settings → Integrations — \"Use local Ollama models\" section"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:82
msgid ".. image:: /_static/img/ai-agent/qs-settings-ollama.png"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:87
msgid "Option B: Claude (Cloud LLM)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:89
msgid "Go to **Settings → AI** (Providers section)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:90
msgid "Find the **\"Use your own Anthropic Claude account\"** section and enter your API key. The provider is activated automatically once a key is entered."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:92
msgid "*(Optional)* **Max Output Tokens** — default 16,384. The Odoo UI accepts up to 128,000, but actual limits depend on the model (Opus: 128k, Sonnet/Haiku: 64k). Values above the model limit are automatically capped at the API level."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:98
msgid "The settings page may display RAG/embedding-related options. These are outside the scope of Quick Start and are covered in the [Configuration](configuration.md) guide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:102
msgid "Settings → AI — \"Use your own Anthropic Claude account\" section"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:102
msgid ".. image:: /_static/img/ai-agent/qs-settings-claude.png"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:108
msgid "For advanced parameter tuning and RAG (document retrieval) setup, see the [Configuration](configuration.md) guide."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:112
msgid "Step 3 — Create an AI Agent"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:114
msgid "Go to **AI → Agents → Agents** (Kanban view by default)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:115
msgid "Click **Create**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:116
msgid "Enter an agent name (e.g., `Sales Assistant`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:117
msgid "Select a model from the **LLM Model** dropdown:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:118
msgid "Ollama: `qwen3.5:9b` (recommended) or `qwen3.5:35b` (high performance)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:119
msgid "Claude: `Claude Sonnet 4.6` (balanced) or `Claude Opus 4.6` (highest capability)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:120
msgid "*(Optional)* Configure System Prompt, Topics, etc. — keep the defaults for Quick Start."
msgstr ""

#: ../../ai-agent/quickstart.md:124
msgid "For testing, `qwen3.5:9b` (local, free) or `Claude Haiku 4.5` (cloud, low cost) are good starting points. For production, `qwen3.5:35b` or `Claude Sonnet 4.6` provide higher tool-call accuracy. The available model list is populated automatically based on your provider configuration."
msgstr ""

